social_posts.post_text: There’s nothing simpler to “hit the spot” than an elegant burrata salad. A great light meal before our first round of meetings at #ConsciousLifeExpo in #LosAngeles! We spoke about #UnityConsciousness. Speaking of #consciousness, are you conscious of what you eat?

It couldn’t have been a more perfect summer evening at Poggio in Sausalito, right over the bridge from San Francisco. We stopped for a bottle of Sonoma Valley Chardonnay, salads, tartare and some pasta at this northern Italian trattoria with dishes crafted from herbs & produce grown in an on-site garden. 
.
Imagine white corn custard, fontina fonduta, snap peas, sliced veal, tonnato sauce, fried capers, frisee, radish with meyer lemon, fried saffron risotto balls, fontina fonduta, parmigiano Reggiano and fines herbs and one of my favorites, Burrata Cheese with roasted eggplant puree, snap peas, peppers, pistachios, kale and crostini. 
.
They also serve up wood fired veal and pork meatballs with castelvetrano olives and ricotta salata, grilled octopus, frisee, shaved fennel, beluga lentils, preserved lemon and almonds as well as watermelon, taggiasca olives, feta cheese, green beans, mint and basil. For something lighter, go for the yellowfin tuna, horseradish creme fraiche, capers, arugula and pine nuts. The veal had me at hello. 
.
We didn’t have the time to properly review the restaurant as it was a quick stop before the Sausalito Jazz Festival, but we will be back. It’s magical for the ambiance, the service, the wine, and the creative Italian fare. Two thumbs up.

A smattering of divine tastes in #Napa, #Sonoma, #Marin and #Livermore County - the beet salad is from a little gem we reviewed two years ago in #Danville, a charming little town that has its fair share of cute eateries, bistros and cafes. Also less known is #LivermoreValley’s #wine country. Man, it feels so great to be traveling again. More coming and it’s long overdue.

A scrumptious tasting at Black Trumpet in Portsmouth NH. An eclectic menu includes bites like fried stuffed squash blossom with smoked cherry tomatoes, brandade crusted halibut with Swiss chard and succotash, soy-brined Iberico pork loin, cornbread stuffed squid and roasted eggplant soup with charred onion. All exquisite!

A scrumptious anniversary dinner at Poggio in Sausalito just over the bridge from San Francisco - we love this spot.
.
Think homemade white corn custard with fontina fonduta, and grana padano, tagliatelle with white wine cream sauce and garlic, seared halibut with butter beans and capers, spinach ricotta pillows with beef ragu, confit duck leg with kale, endive, pluots, pistachios, and aceto balsamico - Omg (that one had us at hello). They also have a wonderful fresh tartare appetizer with crème fraiche and seared scallops with guanciale, stone fruit, lemon butter and fine herbs. They have a great wine list too, both by the glass and bottle.
Absolutely divine right? A time when you can mix fruits and veggies with cheese and call it a day! Scrumptious bite size served, perfect for a summer barbecue

Our first Rosh Hashanah dinner and we hosted which was quite a feat since neither of us were raised Jewish or came from the tradition. Started with intention, ceremony and food and ended with games and laughter, a whole lotta it! Honey cake with apples anyone?

Our Fall Equinox party was filled with delicious scrumptious treats - thanks to our dear friends Dunja, Gabriele, Loretta and others who showed up bearing such scrumptious gifts. Happy Fall everyone - are you ready for the season and all that it brings?

We ventured to Black Trumpet in Portsmouth which offers a seasonal, eclectic menu with gluten free, vegetarian, vegan and nut free options to boot. They offer a fabulous Cheese and Charcuterie Plate or you can opt for their Shrimp Ceviche Tostada with Cucumber-Nasturtium Pico to kick off your meal. Anthony and I had to try the Tea-Smoked Duck Breast with Beet-Noodle Seaweed Salad and Black Garlic Nigella Emulsion. Simply put, it was to die for.
Fresh seafood at market after market in and around Hampton New Hampshire. What a treat! Crab, #clams, #mussels and #lobster daily. So so great to be back in #NewEngland. #Foodie

Had such a great time visiting one of my old stomping ground restaurants: #Dali in #Somerville on the #Cambridge border. Spanish #tapas are always a great treat but the wonder of this place is the ambiance. From the tiles, ceiling, wall paper, copper accents, art and decor to the ever so authentic and colorful bar, you’ll be charmed all evening long. It was a treasure to be back.

We headed back to #QuincyMarket in downtown #Boston, a place I used to go to frequently when I lived here to meet people for drinks after work. I had to go into the food hall of course which has tons of delicious options, ranging from #seafood, deli, and salads, to Italian, #desserts and #breads.

For cocktails, a must visit is the ever so unique bar in Kittery Maine called The Wallingford Dram. Let’s just say that every one of their cocktails had us at hello. Unusual mixes include the following (they were too amazing not to post in detail):
.
—A Fist in the Mouth of Time: Bourbon, Smoke, Fernet, Coffee Brandy, Bitters, Lavender
—We Are Still Us: Buttered Hay Washed Brandy, Black Pepper, Cumin and Orange Curacao with Egg White and Lemon
—Victims of Late Success: Bourbon, Aperol, Mango, Pine, Preserved Lemon, Coco Blast, Nogori Sake (yes, really), Seltzer and Mint
—Jupiter Jazz: Jalapeno-infused Mezcal, Amaro Montenegro 
—By Witchcraft: Cranberry Infused Gin, Dry Curacao, Lime, Cassia, Creme De Violette (perfect for the region)
.
You get the idea. They were scrumptious!

In Kittery Maine, you’ll find restaurant gem Anneke Jans. Start your night with cocktails at The Walllingford Dram and then walk over to Anneke Jans for dinner. They offer European-influenced American dinners, small plates and drinks in a snazzy, cosmopolitan setting.
.
We started off with Oysters and Mussels because how could you not if they’re on the menu? The chef prepares their Maine mussels with bacon, onions, white wine, cream, and Great Hill blue cheese. Yum, right?
.
Other scrumptious bites at this magical spot include Lobster Salad with Green Corn Relish and Avocado Mousse, Grilled Scallops with Succatosh, Sweet Corn Soubise, Citrus and Leeks, their Scottish Salmon with Mango Quinoa Salad, Shiitake Mushrooms, Bok Choy and Miso Ginger Glaze, and Steak Frites with Romesco.
.
Two thumbs up!

What an amazing night at the opening of @fogo in #Emeryville. Plenty of unique #Steak cuts & #Lamb chops #Tenderloin #PrimeRib et al. 
.
They also offer an incredible salad bar (they call the Market Bar) and beyond where it’s not about #allYoucanEat but rather #AllyoucanExperience with all they have to offer including #cocktails #wine #salads #seafood and of course various meat cuts including #Wagu 
.
So much #yumminess tonight at #fogodechao and the service was through the roof! #BayArea #EastBay #EastBayFoodie #SFFoodie #SteakHouses
More #foodie and #cocktail love @fogo in #Emeryville! The #vibe was lovely, fun and energizing and the food was through the roof
The food plating at Fogo De Chao continues!

Hope you and your family have a wonderful Thanksgiving holiday weekend for those celebrating in the states. Pomegranates were part of our experience this year, fresh off the tree in Napa Valley. How did you all celebrate?

Feeling blessed on my birthday. I always so appreciate the creative appetizer boards my friend Dunja puts together, always made with creativity and love. Wow right? From #pate, nuts and #cheese to #olives, #prosciutto #salami and a creamy #beet dip. #Scrumptious and heavenly combined.
Great dinner surrounded by twinkling white lights outside under umbrellas in Miami’s #CoconutGrove area. Grilled #salmon with mixed greens, #cranberries, tomatoes, Parmesan and #pineNuts.

Yesterday’s #Miami Food Tour in #LittleHavana starting with Colada, a #Cuban #coffee to share and a beef #empanada followed by #sugarcane juice, #peanuts, #cheese and #guava #pastry and #Mojitos baby! Loved walking through the main drag and exploring the side streets. #FoodTours

Delicious #food on board the #RoyalClipper which is part of the #StarClipper fleet, a unique sailing ship #cruise experience. They travel to various destinations but this week we are heading to quite a few islands in the #Caribbean, starting in #Barbados.
Delicious fare on the #RoyalClipper this week #sailing through the #Caribbean. We kicked the first night off in #SaintLucia then #Dominica followed by #Antigua. More coming!
It seems as if we’ve been living on #PinaColadas ever since we set foot on #Barbados soil. Trying out a variation made with #coconut water along the stretch between #Accra and #Rockley beach.

Happy Holidays from our home to yours. As I reflect on this year, I am reminded of the power of thoughts, words, and actions.
.
What we focus on is where our intention goes and where our intention goes is what we ultimately create (and co-create). I truly believe creation is a complex yet beautiful manifestation dance with others . . . other energies. May we remember this delicate web that we are always an integral part of in each and every moment.
.
While we saw actions in the world this year that made us doubt the goodness of humanity, we also felt and experienced love and unity in other areas of our lives. May we remember and cherish those moments. By focusing on those heartfelt times, we can amplify the beauty, the joy, the interconnectedness, the love . . .
.
What we focus on, we bring in more of into our lives . . . literally. Our words carry a frequency of sorts as do our actions. Even a smile carries energy and can melt someone’s heart at a tender time or soften a tense situation when no words will come. Our intentions matter. Our choices matter.
.
I am grateful for these precious moments and to those who took the time to send words of kindness, a smile, a hug, or advice at just the perfect time over this past year. You know who you are. Thank you.
.
Is there anything more important than recognizing the vulnerability, the beauty and the love that uniquely make us human?
.
Happiest of holidays to you dear community. I look forward to seeing what 2024 will bring. My intention is unity, connection, and collective healing on a global scale.
.
May this innate wisdom and realization come to everyone, especially those with the gifts and power to heal trauma, reverse corruption and bring peace. It’s not rocket science, is it? Simply put, as a species, we are stronger when we love. When we collaborate. When we serve others. When we unite . . .
